
#### 01: installer script
curl -L -s https://raw.githubusercontent.com/centreon/centreon/25.10-latest/centreon/unattended.sh | sh
#### 02: centreon installer script generated output DB root password:
As you will need a password for the user [root] on your  database system, a random password is generated
Passwords are currently saved in [/etc/centreon/generated.tobesecured]
Random password generated for user [Database user: root] is [fw03G**VA?!Zf93p]
#### 03: complete web installation wizard "http://<ip>/centreon" using above generated DB root password and for example use web password "Centreon@123"
#### 04: modify for large scale hosts
nano /etc/centreon-engine/centengine.cfg
use_large_installation_tweaks=1
enable_environment_macros=0
use_setpgid=0
check_result_reaper_frequency=1
#### 05: optimise mariaDB
nano /etc/my.cnf.d/centreon.cnf
innodb_buffer_pool_size=1G
#### 06: sudo reboot and login to webpage
#### 07: goto Configuration > Connectors > Monitoring Connectors
enable/activate "Base Pack"
#### 08: goto Configuration  >  Commands  >  Checks
Create new:
Command Name: check_icmp
Command line: $USER1$/check_icmp -H $HOSTADDRESS$ -w 200.0,20% -c 500.0,50% -n 2
Save
#### 09: goto Configuration  >  Hosts  >  Templates
a: Go inside all templates, for Check Period select 24x7 and save.
b: For template "generic-active-host-custom" (which has Linked Services Templates value 1) select timezone Asia/Kolkata, check command select "check_icmp", Check period "24x7", Max Check Attempts 3 , Normal Check Interval 2,  Retry Check Interval 1. Save
#### 10: goto Configuration  >  Services  >  Templates
in template "Base-Ping-LAN-custom", Check period "24x7", Max Check Attempts 3 , Normal Check Interval 2,  Retry Check Interval 1. Save
#### 11: create host group "jeebr"
#### 12: export all to poller and restart poller
#### 13: file "import_to_2510.clapi.txt" has all old centreon hosts with applied template "generic-active-host-custom", poller "Central" and host group "jeebr"
#### 14: import hosts into centreon by CLAPI: (this can take time)
/usr/bin/centreon -u admin -p 'Centreon@123' -i import_to_2510.clapi.txt
#### 15: generate services for each host by CLAPI: (this can take lot of time)
for host in $(/usr/bin/centreon -u admin -p 'Centreon@123' -o HOST -a show | cut -d';' -f2 | grep -v "name"); do
    /usr/bin/centreon -u admin -p 'Centreon@123' -o HOST -a applytpl -v "$host"
done
#### 16: export config to poller with poller restart (tick mark all)
